&gt; than by the hour. You give them the design, they give you a quote, and
then
&gt; you work out a deal. Depending on where and how the art is used, there may
be
&gt; royalties involved. Some artists will work for much less if they can
retain
&gt; the right to re-sell the art to others.
&gt;
&gt; Check out http://www.turbosquid.com/ and browse a bit. You might find what
you
&gt; want there. If not, you can certainly find a willing artist in the forums
or
&gt; by contacting them directly about the work you find on Turbo Squid. The
forums
&gt; and the art will give you a good idea on what you can expect to pay for
&gt; various levels of quality. The art at Turbo Squid is all royalty free with
a
&gt; one time, reasonable cost. Most of the artists found there will make
custom
&gt; work along the same lines (reasonably cheap, by the job, and royalty
free).
